<p>I am returning some information from an RSS feed and currently I am retrieving all fields as strings. One of the fields is a hyperlink for each RSS item. I'd like to be able to turn this into a link so I can actually click on it and go to RSS feed news article. </p>  <p>I am trying to consider which is a better option, between making the entire RSS item that is rendered on the screen a link to the site, or just the particular link aspect itself.</p>  <p>You can reference my implementation <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/32544755/error-reading-rss-feed-using-linq-to-xml?noredirect=1#comment53004146_32544755">here</a> but I'm not sure how to either cast the link when I retrieve it as an RSS item or convert the string to a link in the View, or make each RSS item in the view a link(which would probably be best for easy selection)?</p>  <p>Model.cs</p>  <pre><code>public class RssModel { public string Title { get; set; } public string Link { get; set; } public string Description { get; set; } public string Image { get; set; }  }  public class ReadRssModel { public static List&lt;RssModel&gt; GetRss() {     var client = new WebClient();      var xmlData = client.DownloadString("http://finance.yahoo.com/rss/headline?s=msft,goog,aapl");      XDocument xml = XDocument.Parse(xmlData);      var rssData = (from item in xml.Descendants("item")                    select new RssModel                    {                        Title = ((string)item.Element("title")),                        Link = ((string)item.Element("link")), //convert this to hyperlink?                        Description = ((string)item.Element("description")),                         Image = ((string)item.Element("enclosure").Attribute("url"))                    }).Take(20).ToList();      return rssData;  } } </code></pre>  <p>Index.cshtml</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="row"&gt; &lt;div class="col-md-8"&gt; &lt;h4&gt;Feed&lt;/h4&gt;  @* Make each item a hyperlink (button or something clickable *@ @foreach (var item in Model.RssFeed) {     @item.Title &lt;br /&gt;     @item.Description &lt;br/&gt;     @item.Link &lt;br /&gt; @* Convert this to a hyperlink *@ }  &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>